Included in the box is a fantastic selection of 12 double sided sheets of heavyweight paper per pack, printed on 100% recycled papers in the UK and paired with 8 brown kraft recycled envelopes and geometric stickers.

name: Kente Print by Kitty McCall
description:
This beautiful limited edition Giclée print is designed and made in the UK by textile design brand Kitty McCall.

Inspired by African textile geometries, Kente takes its name from fabric made of interwoven cloth strips and is native to the Akan ethnic group of South Ghana. Kente cloth is identified by its dazzling, multicolored patterns of bright colors, geometric shapes, and bold designs.

Printed on archival Giclée 255gsm fine art paper made from 100% cotton. This high quality paper is acid free and museum quality with a natural white textured watercolour feel.

LImited edition of 200. 

Available in two sizes: 40x50cm and 50x70cm.

*The print shown is 50 x 70 with a 10cm mount*
*Sold unframed only*

This piece is the Eighth and final hour from a series of photographs that captured all contrails over the same piece of sky during eight daylight hours.

A large version of Eighth Hour is currently on show in our first Studio No. 44 exhibition, Photography to Print.
